WEBVTT

00:00:00.820 --> 00:00:10.680
Alif Lam Meem, Allah, la ilaha illa Huwa Al-Hibb Al-Qayyum,

00:00:10.680 --> 00:00:18.180
Nazala alayka al-Kitab Bil-Haqq Musabdiqa lima bayna yadehi wa anzala al-Tawrat wa al-Injeel,

00:00:18.180 --> 00:00:22.260
min qabnu hudan lil-Nas wa anzala al-Furqan,

00:00:22.260 --> 00:00:27.540
inna allatheena kafiru bi ayatillahi lahum ʿadabuhu shadeed,

00:00:27.540 --> 00:00:31.420
wa Allah hua ʿazeezu ʿindhu ʿuntiqan,

00:00:31.740 --> 00:00:36.580
inna allaha la yakhda ʿalayhi shajad fi al-ardi wa la fi al-samad.

00:00:36.580 --> 00:00:40.060
We are moving through the story of the life of the most blessed of creation,

00:00:40.060 --> 00:00:46.580
the final of messengers Muhammad ibn Abdullah al-Hashimi al-Qurashi sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:00:46.580 --> 00:00:53.100
A point of clarification, I was asked a question earlier today regarding the well of Zamzam.

00:00:53.100 --> 00:00:59.500
The question was, we made mention of Abdul Muttalib having had the privilege to dig,

00:00:59.500 --> 00:01:02.700
because he saw in his dream where the well was.

00:01:02.700 --> 00:01:05.180
When he dug it, it began to gush.

00:01:05.180 --> 00:01:09.780
So, didn't we hear before that Ibrahim a.s.'s time,

00:01:09.780 --> 00:01:13.540
there was Hajar a.s., the mother of Ismail,

00:01:13.540 --> 00:01:17.900
who was running between Safa and Marwa and then the well began to gush?

00:01:17.900 --> 00:01:21.860
The answer is yes, that is when the well started.

00:01:21.860 --> 00:01:26.540
That is the first appearance of the water of Zamzam was at the time of Ismail a.s.,

00:01:26.540 --> 00:01:28.300
when he was a little child.

00:01:28.340 --> 00:01:32.900
But if you take a careful look, you will come to learn that after some time,

00:01:32.900 --> 00:01:37.220
it was blocked because of the floods and because of various other reasons

00:01:37.220 --> 00:01:39.220
connected to the weather and so on.

00:01:39.220 --> 00:01:44.940
And what had happened thereafter is that at the time of Abdul Muttalib,

00:01:44.940 --> 00:01:47.660
it was made to gush forth once again.

00:01:47.660 --> 00:01:52.260
So this was the second time that the Zamzam had gushed.

00:01:52.260 --> 00:01:56.140
Now we are moving on to Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:01:56.180 --> 00:02:03.420
where he used to, as we said, see dreams and the following day it would be completely true.

00:02:03.420 --> 00:02:05.540
Whatever he saw was true.

00:02:05.540 --> 00:02:09.580
Why was this the beginning of prophethood or early signs?

00:02:09.580 --> 00:02:14.260
Because according to what we are taught by Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:02:14.260 --> 00:02:18.380
when a prophet of Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam sees a dream,

00:02:18.380 --> 00:02:21.260
it is revelation, it is the truth.

00:02:21.260 --> 00:02:25.100
They have to act upon it and it is not false at all.

00:02:25.100 --> 00:02:30.900
Like you know, Ibrahim a.s. saw in his dream that he was sacrificing his son.

00:02:30.900 --> 00:02:33.940
That was considered an instruction of Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:02:33.940 --> 00:02:35.260
It was revelation.

00:02:35.260 --> 00:02:38.820
So the same applies early when Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:02:38.820 --> 00:02:44.140
began to see a dream and then the following day it would be completely true.

00:02:44.140 --> 00:02:45.860
This was the early signs.

00:02:45.860 --> 00:02:50.300
Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam was purifying him and raising his level.

00:02:50.300 --> 00:02:56.100
Thereafter he used to go into the Mount of Hira, the cave of Hira

00:02:56.100 --> 00:02:58.980
as we heard yesterday north west of Mecca.

00:02:58.980 --> 00:03:03.020
We ask Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam to take us to Mecca time and again

00:03:03.020 --> 00:03:06.860
and we ask Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam to refresh us and rejuvenate us

00:03:06.860 --> 00:03:09.020
so that we can worship him at all times,

00:03:09.020 --> 00:03:12.500
worship our Maker and none other than the Maker.

00:03:12.500 --> 00:03:14.380
May Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam bless us.

00:03:14.380 --> 00:03:17.220
So Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam used to see the dreams

00:03:17.220 --> 00:03:20.860
and thereafter he used to go into this cave and meditate.

00:03:20.860 --> 00:03:23.420
Meditate in seclusion, subhanallah.

00:03:23.420 --> 00:03:26.220
He used to ponder over the condition of the people of Mecca

00:03:26.220 --> 00:03:28.940
and try and ponder over solutions, number one.

00:03:28.940 --> 00:03:32.380
Number two is he used to worship Allah and praise Allah

00:03:32.380 --> 00:03:35.860
according to the teachings of Ibrahim a.s.

00:03:35.860 --> 00:03:38.300
and that was the monotheism, the one Allah.

00:03:38.300 --> 00:03:42.780
He used to praise the Creator and the one whom he will return to

00:03:42.820 --> 00:03:47.380
and this was what he used to engage in the worship of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:03:47.380 --> 00:03:50.260
People might wonder, well what worship did he engage in?

00:03:50.260 --> 00:03:51.420
He worshiped Allah alone.

00:03:51.420 --> 00:03:55.460
He never ever bowed to an idol, nor did he bow to people,

00:03:55.460 --> 00:03:58.740
nor did he engage in tawaf around the Kaaba

00:03:58.740 --> 00:04:00.540
whilst those idols were there.

00:04:00.540 --> 00:04:02.180
No, he did not.

00:04:02.180 --> 00:04:05.660
Meaning in the pre-Islamic time he did not do it for the idols

00:04:05.660 --> 00:04:08.220
but he did it for the pleasure of his Maker

00:04:08.220 --> 00:04:09.980
for the sake of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:04:09.980 --> 00:04:12.980
when Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala instructed him to do that.

00:04:12.980 --> 00:04:15.980
Also we learnt that some of the various creatures

00:04:15.980 --> 00:04:19.140
of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala used to greet him

00:04:19.140 --> 00:04:21.100
like we spoke about the stone twice.

00:04:21.100 --> 00:04:22.860
This is the third time I'm mentioning it

00:04:22.860 --> 00:04:24.820
and Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wasallam says,

00:04:24.820 --> 00:04:27.660
I know a stone or a rock in Mecca

00:04:27.660 --> 00:04:31.340
that used to actually greet me sallallahu alaihi wasallam.

00:04:31.340 --> 00:04:36.100
So one day what happened is as he was in the cave

00:04:36.100 --> 00:04:40.220
and this was the 21st day of Ramadan,

00:04:40.220 --> 00:04:44.860
the 21st night, in fact the eve, Ramadan,

00:04:44.860 --> 00:04:48.100
when he was 40 years old

00:04:48.100 --> 00:04:52.140
and suddenly in that cave appeared the angel,

00:04:52.140 --> 00:04:54.780
Jibril alaihi wasallam

00:04:54.780 --> 00:04:56.700
and Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:04:56.700 --> 00:04:58.980
obviously it was something different for him.

00:04:58.980 --> 00:05:01.980
He was concerned, he was worried to a great degree

00:05:01.980 --> 00:05:04.900
and Jibril alaihi wasallam came to him

00:05:04.900 --> 00:05:07.580
and tells him, Iqra, read.

00:05:07.580 --> 00:05:11.620
First words, revelation coming down from Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:05:11.620 --> 00:05:14.580
Revelation came down in several forms.

00:05:14.580 --> 00:05:16.340
One of them was this way,

00:05:16.340 --> 00:05:20.180
when Jibril alaihi wasallam was sent by Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:05:20.180 --> 00:05:22.540
and he came and he instilled it

00:05:22.540 --> 00:05:25.460
into the heart of Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:05:25.460 --> 00:05:28.060
in a way that it will never be forgotten.

00:05:28.060 --> 00:05:30.580
This is why today when you learn something in memory,

00:05:30.580 --> 00:05:33.220
they say this person learnt it off by heart,

00:05:33.260 --> 00:05:35.660
which means solid, placed in the heart.

00:05:35.660 --> 00:05:38.020
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala solidify

00:05:38.020 --> 00:05:40.140
the memorization that we have of the Quran.

00:05:40.140 --> 00:05:43.780
Every one of us have contributed in one way or another

00:05:43.780 --> 00:05:46.380
towards the preservation of the Quran

00:05:46.380 --> 00:05:49.380
by memorizing even if it means Surah al-Fatiha.

00:05:49.380 --> 00:05:51.660
Today we read it so many times, I'm sure,

00:05:51.660 --> 00:05:54.100
every one of us knows it off by heart.

00:05:54.100 --> 00:05:55.060
And if we don't,

00:05:55.060 --> 00:05:57.100
then there is something wrong with us being Muslim.

00:05:57.100 --> 00:05:59.460
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us protection.

00:05:59.460 --> 00:06:02.460
So we have all memorized a portion of the Quran,

00:06:02.460 --> 00:06:06.340
every single one of us without exception, subhanallah.

00:06:06.340 --> 00:06:08.340
So this is the gift of Allah.

00:06:08.340 --> 00:06:11.340
The Prophet Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam's heart

00:06:11.340 --> 00:06:14.060
had within it the Quran placed

00:06:14.060 --> 00:06:15.660
by Jibreel alayhi salatu wa salam

00:06:15.660 --> 00:06:18.740
by the will of Allah, the power of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:06:18.740 --> 00:06:22.300
So this man, 40 years old, that's not a child,

00:06:22.300 --> 00:06:25.940
he's old and he was being told read.

00:06:25.940 --> 00:06:27.700
So what happened?

00:06:27.700 --> 00:06:30.500
He said, ma ana bi qari, I can't read,

00:06:30.500 --> 00:06:32.620
I'm not a reader.

00:06:32.620 --> 00:06:34.780
He was unlettered, remember Allah says,

00:06:34.780 --> 00:06:36.620
the bulk of them were unlettered.

00:06:36.620 --> 00:06:41.620
Huwa allathee ba'athafil ummiyeena rasoolan minhum.

00:06:44.180 --> 00:06:46.740
It is Allah who sent a messenger

00:06:46.740 --> 00:06:50.140
amongst the unlettered one from amongst them to them.

00:06:50.140 --> 00:06:52.300
So the bulk of them were unlettered.

00:06:52.300 --> 00:06:55.620
He was honest enough to say, I am unlettered.

00:06:55.620 --> 00:06:58.660
How many of us here would want to admit

00:06:58.660 --> 00:07:01.260
that we know nothing about technology at all?

00:07:01.260 --> 00:07:02.820
Imagine holding your mobile phone

00:07:02.820 --> 00:07:04.940
the other way around on your ear.

00:07:04.940 --> 00:07:06.060
Would anyone want to admit

00:07:06.060 --> 00:07:08.700
that we don't know how to operate this gadget?

00:07:08.700 --> 00:07:10.900
No matter what, I have actually seen people

00:07:10.900 --> 00:07:12.780
who read books the other way around.

00:07:12.780 --> 00:07:14.900
And it's only the photograph that makes them know

00:07:14.900 --> 00:07:16.260
that this is how you're gonna hold it.

00:07:16.260 --> 00:07:17.900
And even then they make mistakes

00:07:17.900 --> 00:07:20.140
and they're supposed to be rulers of the world at times.

00:07:20.140 --> 00:07:22.580
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness

00:07:22.580 --> 00:07:24.180
and may He make us from amongst those

00:07:24.180 --> 00:07:25.620
who realize and understand.

00:07:25.620 --> 00:07:27.100
Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:07:27.100 --> 00:07:28.340
was not a proud man.

00:07:28.340 --> 00:07:29.540
He was honest.

00:07:29.540 --> 00:07:31.820
He was dignified, straightforward,

00:07:31.820 --> 00:07:33.420
trustworthy, truthful.

00:07:33.420 --> 00:07:35.140
He says, maa ana biqari.

00:07:35.140 --> 00:07:38.300
So Jibril alaihi wasallam embraced him

00:07:38.300 --> 00:07:43.100
and hugged him tight until he was almost suffocating

00:07:43.100 --> 00:07:46.340
and then released him and told him again, iqra.

00:07:46.340 --> 00:07:49.900
So he says, maa ana biqari, I am not a reader.

00:07:49.900 --> 00:07:52.180
You're asking me to read, I am not a reader.

00:07:52.180 --> 00:07:55.100
So Jibril alaihi wasallam, the archangel Gabriel,

00:07:55.100 --> 00:07:57.780
may peace be upon him, embraced him once again

00:07:57.820 --> 00:08:00.780
and hugged him tight until he almost suffocated

00:08:00.780 --> 00:08:02.180
and then released him again.

00:08:02.180 --> 00:08:04.500
And he says, iqra for the third time.

00:08:04.500 --> 00:08:06.500
And Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:08:06.500 --> 00:08:09.860
for the third time says, maa ana biqari.

00:08:09.860 --> 00:08:13.140
He embraced him for the third time and released him.

00:08:13.140 --> 00:08:14.700
The verses were revealed.

00:08:14.700 --> 00:08:18.860
Iqra, bismi rabbika allathee khalaqa.

00:08:18.860 --> 00:08:23.300
Khalaqa al-insana min alaqa.

00:08:23.300 --> 00:08:29.340
Iqra, warabbuka al-akramu allathee aallama bil-qalam.

00:08:29.340 --> 00:08:35.540
Aallama al-insana maa lam ya'alam.

00:08:35.540 --> 00:08:36.660
Stop there.

00:08:36.660 --> 00:08:37.420
Subhanallah.

00:08:37.420 --> 00:08:39.580
Five verses revealed one time.

00:08:39.580 --> 00:08:40.420
What were they?

00:08:40.420 --> 00:08:44.260
Read, read in the name of your Lord who has created.

00:08:44.260 --> 00:08:48.140
The term Lord is not the proper translation of Rabb

00:08:48.140 --> 00:08:51.420
because Rabb means the creator, nourisher, cherisher,

00:08:51.420 --> 00:08:53.100
sustainer, provider, protector,

00:08:53.100 --> 00:08:56.140
the one in supreme control, absolute control

00:08:56.140 --> 00:08:59.300
of every aspect of every creature in creation.

00:08:59.300 --> 00:09:03.740
That is the term Rabbun used to refer to that deity.

00:09:03.740 --> 00:09:06.700
So Allah says, read in the name of your Rabb

00:09:06.700 --> 00:09:08.380
who has created.

00:09:08.380 --> 00:09:10.140
Created absolutely everything.

00:09:10.140 --> 00:09:12.180
But here created what?

00:09:13.020 --> 00:09:15.380
Iqra, bismi rabbika allathee khalaqa.

00:09:15.380 --> 00:09:17.500
Firstly created absolutely everything

00:09:17.500 --> 00:09:21.060
but he created man from a clot of blood.

00:09:21.060 --> 00:09:22.940
Khalaqa al-insana min alaqa.

00:09:22.940 --> 00:09:25.460
He created man from a clot of blood.

00:09:25.460 --> 00:09:27.380
Now some people look at the Quran and say,

00:09:27.380 --> 00:09:28.500
well there is a contradiction

00:09:28.500 --> 00:09:30.900
because in one place Allah says created from dust,

00:09:30.900 --> 00:09:32.500
one place He says soil,

00:09:32.500 --> 00:09:33.980
one place He says clay,

00:09:33.980 --> 00:09:35.780
one place He says semen,

00:09:35.780 --> 00:09:38.700
one place He says a clot of blood and so on.

00:09:38.700 --> 00:09:39.820
There is no contradiction.

00:09:39.820 --> 00:09:41.820
These are the different phases and stages

00:09:41.940 --> 00:09:43.420
in the creation of man.

00:09:43.420 --> 00:09:46.020
Initially dust, soil, clay.

00:09:46.020 --> 00:09:47.980
Once the first human being was created,

00:09:47.980 --> 00:09:50.060
the second one was created from his rib

00:09:50.060 --> 00:09:51.700
and once those two were created,

00:09:51.700 --> 00:09:52.940
the semen was used.

00:09:52.940 --> 00:09:55.620
When semen and as you know,

00:09:55.620 --> 00:09:57.340
when the zygote is formed

00:09:57.340 --> 00:09:59.180
and the embryo begins to grow,

00:09:59.180 --> 00:10:00.940
it's a clot of blood initially

00:10:00.940 --> 00:10:03.620
and thereafter it begins to gain form and so on.

00:10:03.620 --> 00:10:04.820
Subhanallah.

00:10:04.820 --> 00:10:06.540
So this is Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:10:06.540 --> 00:10:08.820
making mention of the different stages

00:10:08.820 --> 00:10:10.420
within the creation of man.

00:10:10.420 --> 00:10:11.460
No contradiction.

00:10:11.500 --> 00:10:12.940
خَلَقَ الْإِنسَانَ مِنْ عَلَكَ

00:10:12.940 --> 00:10:15.100
اِقْرَءُ وَرَبُكَ الْأَكْرَمُ

00:10:15.100 --> 00:10:18.500
Read and you should know that your Rabb

00:10:18.500 --> 00:10:21.820
is the most generous, al-Akram,

00:10:21.820 --> 00:10:23.940
the most generous, the most honouring.

00:10:23.940 --> 00:10:24.820
Allahu Akbar.

00:10:24.820 --> 00:10:27.300
Allah has just honoured him with prophethood

00:10:27.300 --> 00:10:29.780
and Allah has honoured and favoured us all

00:10:29.780 --> 00:10:32.700
and humanity at large by granting them nubuwa.

00:10:32.700 --> 00:10:34.740
Imagine what love Allah had had

00:10:34.740 --> 00:10:36.380
for the people of Quraysh

00:10:36.380 --> 00:10:38.060
for raising from their midst

00:10:38.060 --> 00:10:40.780
a nabi, a precious jewel,

00:10:40.780 --> 00:10:43.620
a person who would come and change the whole globe.

00:10:43.620 --> 00:10:44.580
Subhanallah.

00:10:44.580 --> 00:10:47.260
Imagine the love of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:10:47.260 --> 00:10:49.100
for those who were the household

00:10:49.100 --> 00:10:51.020
of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:10:51.020 --> 00:10:54.300
who accepted his message instantaneously

00:10:54.300 --> 00:10:57.060
as we will see a little bit later.

00:10:57.060 --> 00:11:00.180
And this is why we say at that moment

00:11:00.180 --> 00:11:01.460
what had happened on earth

00:11:01.460 --> 00:11:04.340
was something changing the entire earth.

00:11:04.340 --> 00:11:07.540
Allah blessed the inhabitants of the earth

00:11:07.540 --> 00:11:09.780
by sending Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:11:09.780 --> 00:11:10.620
at that time.

00:11:10.620 --> 00:11:12.020
The period of darkness

00:11:12.020 --> 00:11:13.700
where women were being oppressed

00:11:13.700 --> 00:11:16.620
from left to right, east to west, north to south.

00:11:16.620 --> 00:11:18.100
Everywhere there were wars,

00:11:18.100 --> 00:11:20.300
there was feud, the order of the day.

00:11:20.300 --> 00:11:21.060
What was it?

00:11:21.060 --> 00:11:22.860
It was chaos, oppression.

00:11:22.860 --> 00:11:24.220
Those who were strong ruled.

00:11:24.220 --> 00:11:26.100
Those who were weak were downtrodden.

00:11:26.100 --> 00:11:28.300
They were oppressed and enslaved at times.

00:11:28.300 --> 00:11:29.820
Three men were enslaved

00:11:29.820 --> 00:11:31.460
just because they were not recognised

00:11:31.460 --> 00:11:33.060
or they did not have a clan

00:11:33.060 --> 00:11:35.100
to protect them against the tyrants.

00:11:35.100 --> 00:11:37.020
And this is what was the order of the day.

00:11:37.020 --> 00:11:39.180
And if you take a look at the gift of Allah,

00:11:39.180 --> 00:11:41.380
these people were worshipping stones

00:11:41.380 --> 00:11:43.220
and sticks and idols and people

00:11:43.220 --> 00:11:44.700
and so many other things.

00:11:44.700 --> 00:11:47.020
And they had lots of superstition in them.

00:11:47.020 --> 00:11:48.540
What a blessed gift of Allah.

00:11:48.540 --> 00:11:50.780
Allah is sending a messenger from amongst them

00:11:50.780 --> 00:11:53.580
to say, worship your maker and your maker alone

00:11:53.580 --> 00:12:00.080
and do not associate partnership with your maker.

00:12:00.080 --> 00:12:03.320
Al-Ladhiy al-Lama bil-Qalam

00:12:03.320 --> 00:12:06.320
Your Rabb, the one who taught by the pen.

00:12:06.320 --> 00:12:10.880
Al-Lama al-Insana ma lam ya'lam

00:12:10.920 --> 00:12:14.080
He taught man what man did not know.

00:12:14.080 --> 00:12:15.760
What man did not know.

00:12:15.760 --> 00:12:17.360
What did man know at the beginning?

00:12:17.360 --> 00:12:18.960
Nothing. As time is passing,

00:12:18.960 --> 00:12:21.560
Allah is allowing us to know more and more

00:12:21.560 --> 00:12:24.480
certain things we will never be able to explain

00:12:24.480 --> 00:12:27.080
such as a dream.

00:12:27.080 --> 00:12:29.440
When you dream, what do you dream?

00:12:29.440 --> 00:12:30.520
How do you dream?

00:12:30.520 --> 00:12:34.320
They still have not developed a little flash stick

00:12:34.320 --> 00:12:35.960
that you can plug into your ear

00:12:35.960 --> 00:12:38.080
and choose to dream what you would like.

00:12:38.080 --> 00:12:39.160
That hasn't yet happened.

00:12:39.160 --> 00:12:40.080
Allahu Akbar.

00:12:40.120 --> 00:12:41.720
And I don't think it's coming.

00:12:41.720 --> 00:12:43.360
This is a gift of Allah.

00:12:43.360 --> 00:12:45.680
You dream, you can be dreaming of the best dream.

00:12:45.680 --> 00:12:48.240
The person next to you can be having the worst dream.

00:12:48.240 --> 00:12:50.440
The two of you will be one in peace

00:12:50.440 --> 00:12:51.600
and the other in torment.

00:12:51.600 --> 00:12:53.320
When you get up, Subhanallah,

00:12:53.320 --> 00:12:55.720
neither can feel what happened to the other.

00:12:55.720 --> 00:12:56.800
That's a gift of Allah.

00:12:56.800 --> 00:12:59.520
Allah says, we taught man what he did not know.

00:12:59.520 --> 00:13:01.040
That's Allah Subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:13:01.040 --> 00:13:02.400
Think of his greatness.

00:13:02.400 --> 00:13:03.640
And Allah is telling us,

00:13:03.640 --> 00:13:10.120
وَمَا أُوْتِيتُمْ مِنَ الْعِلْمِ إِلَّا قَلِيلًا

00:13:10.120 --> 00:13:13.720
And you have not been granted knowledge except but a little.

00:13:13.720 --> 00:13:16.520
Still, whatever you have is just a droplet.

00:13:16.520 --> 00:13:18.640
Subhanallah.

00:13:18.640 --> 00:13:20.640
A long time ago when people used to be told

00:13:20.640 --> 00:13:24.080
of how the angels write down everything you utter

00:13:24.080 --> 00:13:26.360
and it is written and it will come on the day of Qiyamah

00:13:26.360 --> 00:13:27.800
and it will be weighed on the scales,

00:13:27.800 --> 00:13:29.560
literally weighing on the scales.

00:13:29.560 --> 00:13:31.640
People began to say, how will the books look?

00:13:31.640 --> 00:13:32.560
They will look like this

00:13:32.560 --> 00:13:33.640
and they will look like that.

00:13:33.640 --> 00:13:36.320
Today you have a 64 gigabyte little chip

00:13:36.320 --> 00:13:38.280
smaller than the size of my nail

00:13:38.280 --> 00:13:42.680
and in it you can have 6400 libraries full of books

00:13:42.680 --> 00:13:44.080
and still they will be space.

00:13:44.080 --> 00:13:45.520
Subhanallah.

00:13:45.520 --> 00:13:46.360
Look at this.

00:13:46.360 --> 00:13:48.720
And people used to say, how will that happen?

00:13:48.720 --> 00:13:51.160
Today when you talk, the computer registers,

00:13:51.160 --> 00:13:54.680
the iPhone registers, the Android device registers

00:13:54.680 --> 00:13:57.440
and people wonder, how will these angels register?

00:13:57.440 --> 00:13:58.520
Allahu Akbar.

00:13:58.520 --> 00:14:01.080
Look, a few years ago it was not dreamt of

00:14:01.080 --> 00:14:03.440
that your phone will listen to your instruction.

00:14:03.440 --> 00:14:04.800
Today it's there.

00:14:04.800 --> 00:14:06.440
Today people speak to the doors.

00:14:06.440 --> 00:14:08.880
They tell the door to open, it opens with your voice.

00:14:08.880 --> 00:14:10.840
Anyone else's voice, it doesn't open.

00:14:10.840 --> 00:14:13.520
You come to the door, it recognizes you by your eye

00:14:13.520 --> 00:14:14.520
and it opens for you.

00:14:14.520 --> 00:14:15.520
It's happening.

00:14:15.520 --> 00:14:17.400
Where do you think you're going to run away

00:14:17.400 --> 00:14:20.120
from Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala and his forces?

00:14:20.120 --> 00:14:22.960
That Rabb who gave us out of the little knowledge

00:14:22.960 --> 00:14:25.960
that we have, the understanding of so much,

00:14:25.960 --> 00:14:29.520
do you not think he is able to absolutely have

00:14:29.520 --> 00:14:32.600
the record of every droplet that has occurred

00:14:32.600 --> 00:14:35.160
from the beginning of time right to the end of time?

00:14:35.160 --> 00:14:37.120
Subhanarabbiya al-A'la.

00:14:37.120 --> 00:14:39.320
So Allah says, read in the name of your Rabb.

00:14:39.320 --> 00:14:40.440
We learn a lot from this

00:14:40.440 --> 00:14:42.640
and I need to pause for a moment.

00:14:42.640 --> 00:14:45.600
Firstly, the first words that were revealed

00:14:45.600 --> 00:14:47.360
to Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam,

00:14:47.360 --> 00:14:49.320
read, the man is unlettered.

00:14:49.320 --> 00:14:50.840
We would not say uneducated

00:14:50.840 --> 00:14:53.160
because he was highly educated,

00:14:53.160 --> 00:14:54.760
but he was unlettered.

00:14:54.760 --> 00:14:55.840
And why unlettered?

00:14:55.840 --> 00:14:57.680
Allah kept it that way for a reason.

00:14:57.720 --> 00:14:59.920
Because the people of the book,

00:14:59.920 --> 00:15:02.080
a lot of them barely knew Arabic.

00:15:02.080 --> 00:15:03.280
And what had happened is,

00:15:03.280 --> 00:15:05.840
he did not know how to read the other languages.

00:15:05.840 --> 00:15:07.320
So amazingly you will find

00:15:07.320 --> 00:15:09.920
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala has covered him.

00:15:09.920 --> 00:15:12.320
Nobody can say he read from those people.

00:15:12.320 --> 00:15:14.720
No one can say he sat and communicated with them.

00:15:14.720 --> 00:15:16.320
No, he was unlettered.

00:15:16.320 --> 00:15:19.800
This thing came, the whole universe acknowledges

00:15:19.800 --> 00:15:21.320
that this was an unlettered man.

00:15:21.320 --> 00:15:22.880
Subhanarabbiya al-A'la.

00:15:22.880 --> 00:15:25.800
We ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala to bless us

00:15:25.800 --> 00:15:26.720
and to open our doors.

00:15:26.720 --> 00:15:29.280
Yet we, we can read every booklet.

00:15:29.280 --> 00:15:31.360
We still haven't read the main book.

00:15:31.360 --> 00:15:32.320
Think of it.

00:15:32.320 --> 00:15:33.280
He could not read,

00:15:33.280 --> 00:15:35.080
but he knew that book of Bayhat.

00:15:35.080 --> 00:15:37.120
We can read and write and we are proud

00:15:37.120 --> 00:15:39.960
and we send our children to school from an early age.

00:15:39.960 --> 00:15:42.400
We're so excited when they can say A to Z

00:15:42.400 --> 00:15:44.760
all the way at the age of three and two

00:15:44.760 --> 00:15:45.920
and we get so happy.

00:15:45.920 --> 00:15:47.760
But they still haven't read the Quran

00:15:47.760 --> 00:15:48.880
and they still don't know

00:15:48.880 --> 00:15:51.000
what the whole world is all about.

00:15:51.000 --> 00:15:53.400
And some of us are still guilty of that.

00:15:53.400 --> 00:15:55.680
Yet we are 40, 50, 60 years old.

00:15:55.680 --> 00:15:58.360
Not once did we read the meaning of the Quran.

00:15:58.360 --> 00:15:59.800
It happens.

00:15:59.800 --> 00:16:00.840
This is the weakness of man.

00:16:00.840 --> 00:16:03.600
And yet the first word to be revealed is Iqra.

00:16:03.600 --> 00:16:05.440
If you're not going to read the word of Allah,

00:16:05.440 --> 00:16:06.920
what are you going to read?

00:16:06.920 --> 00:16:09.760
So this is a challenge to you all and to myself.

00:16:09.760 --> 00:16:12.160
Read the word of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:16:12.160 --> 00:16:13.520
before your time is up.

00:16:13.520 --> 00:16:15.000
You are not going to have a response

00:16:15.000 --> 00:16:17.720
when Allah asks you, I reveal the word read.

00:16:17.720 --> 00:16:19.200
Did you read my word?

00:16:19.200 --> 00:16:20.040
What are we going to say?

00:16:20.040 --> 00:16:22.760
La ilaha illa Allah.

00:16:22.760 --> 00:16:25.840
There can be no more powerful statement than that.

00:16:25.840 --> 00:16:28.640
Iqra, bismi rabbik, read in the name of Allah.

00:16:28.640 --> 00:16:30.360
When we start reading the Quran,

00:16:30.360 --> 00:16:34.080
a'udhu billahi minash shaytanir rajeem,

00:16:34.080 --> 00:16:38.840
bismillahir rahmanir raheem.

00:16:38.840 --> 00:16:42.480
I seek the protection of Allah from shaytan, the accursed.

00:16:42.480 --> 00:16:45.280
In the name of Allah, the most gracious, most merciful.

00:16:45.280 --> 00:16:46.200
Then we start reading.

00:16:46.200 --> 00:16:49.280
We started in the name of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:16:49.280 --> 00:16:52.360
This also shows us that what seems impossible

00:16:52.360 --> 00:16:53.520
in this world.

00:16:53.520 --> 00:16:56.360
If we say the name of Allah, it becomes possible.

00:16:56.360 --> 00:16:57.560
It becomes easy for us.

00:16:57.560 --> 00:16:59.760
Allah facilitates it for us.

00:16:59.760 --> 00:17:01.240
And this is why there is a hadith

00:17:01.240 --> 00:17:03.720
where the Prophet Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam says,

00:17:03.720 --> 00:17:05.400
kullu amrin, the ibadin,

00:17:05.400 --> 00:17:08.760
lam yubtada ufihi bismillahi fahuwa aqta.

00:17:08.760 --> 00:17:12.240
Anything important that you start without the name of Allah,

00:17:12.240 --> 00:17:15.200
it is cut, cut of blessings, cut of simplicity,

00:17:15.200 --> 00:17:16.760
cut of all forms of goodness,

00:17:16.760 --> 00:17:18.400
you won't achieve anything good.

00:17:18.400 --> 00:17:19.720
So whatever you are doing,

00:17:19.720 --> 00:17:22.120
get in the habit of saying bismillah

00:17:22.120 --> 00:17:23.280
because in this way,

00:17:23.280 --> 00:17:25.880
Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam who was unlettered,

00:17:25.880 --> 00:17:29.000
he started and was instructed to start in the name of Allah

00:17:29.000 --> 00:17:31.840
to read and Allah opened his doors with us.

00:17:31.840 --> 00:17:33.120
If we use the name of Allah,

00:17:33.120 --> 00:17:35.280
Allah opens the doors within our homes,

00:17:35.280 --> 00:17:37.080
within our businesses, within our families,

00:17:37.080 --> 00:17:39.880
within our societies, with our health, our wealth,

00:17:39.880 --> 00:17:42.120
absolutely every aspect of existence.

00:17:42.120 --> 00:17:44.640
Whatever you do, bismillah, get into that habit.

00:17:44.640 --> 00:17:46.680
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala open our doors.

00:17:46.680 --> 00:17:48.160
Another thing we need to know,

00:17:48.160 --> 00:17:51.320
nothing is impossible for Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:17:51.360 --> 00:17:52.320
Nothing.

00:17:52.320 --> 00:17:54.400
Miracles can happen, have happened,

00:17:54.400 --> 00:17:56.160
are happening and shall happen.

00:17:56.160 --> 00:17:57.040
Remember that.

00:17:57.040 --> 00:17:59.400
Nothing is impossible for Allah.

00:17:59.400 --> 00:18:01.680
So just continue praying to Allah.

00:18:01.680 --> 00:18:02.600
Whatever you want,

00:18:02.600 --> 00:18:04.280
don't lose hope in the mercy of Allah.

00:18:04.280 --> 00:18:06.560
Make sure you are on the right page.

00:18:06.560 --> 00:18:09.240
Sometimes we are not only on the wrong page,

00:18:09.240 --> 00:18:10.880
we are in a different book

00:18:10.880 --> 00:18:13.200
and we're calling to Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:18:13.200 --> 00:18:15.760
What this means is our food is haram,

00:18:15.760 --> 00:18:18.280
our drink is haram, everything is haram.

00:18:18.280 --> 00:18:21.240
How are we going to get our dua responded?

00:18:28.000 --> 00:18:30.680
A person whose food is haram, drinking is haram,

00:18:30.680 --> 00:18:33.000
his entire diet is haram,

00:18:33.000 --> 00:18:35.800
everything he has consumed, his clothing, the works, haram.

00:18:35.800 --> 00:18:36.600
Then he wants to say,

00:18:36.600 --> 00:18:37.640
Ya Rabbi, Ya Rabbi,

00:18:37.640 --> 00:18:40.160
how does he expect the dua to be accepted?

00:18:40.160 --> 00:18:42.120
This is why when we are making dua,

00:18:42.120 --> 00:18:43.720
start off also by saying,

00:18:43.720 --> 00:18:44.960
Oh Allah, forgive me.

00:18:44.960 --> 00:18:46.320
Ya Allah, I've committed sin.

00:18:46.320 --> 00:18:48.240
Those which I know, those which I don't.

00:18:48.240 --> 00:18:49.840
Those which I committed in secret,

00:18:49.840 --> 00:18:51.200
those which I committed openly.

00:18:51.200 --> 00:18:52.080
You forgive me.

00:18:52.080 --> 00:18:53.480
You know better than me

00:18:53.480 --> 00:18:55.320
what sins I have committed.

00:18:55.320 --> 00:18:56.920
Ya Allah, forgive me.

00:18:56.920 --> 00:18:58.800
Allahu akbar.

00:18:58.800 --> 00:19:02.320
And this is why when it comes to sins and their effect,

00:19:02.320 --> 00:19:06.440
you need to know those who do not dress appropriately.

00:19:06.440 --> 00:19:08.680
They want to show their aura.

00:19:08.680 --> 00:19:11.040
They want to show their private parts,

00:19:11.040 --> 00:19:13.560
whether it be hair, whether it be legs,

00:19:13.560 --> 00:19:15.800
whether it be the chest or the cleavage,

00:19:15.800 --> 00:19:21.200
whether it be going right up to the top of your hand and so on.

00:19:21.200 --> 00:19:23.120
When a woman is supposed to be covered

00:19:23.120 --> 00:19:24.960
and a man is supposed to be covered,

00:19:24.960 --> 00:19:26.920
those who expose,

00:19:26.920 --> 00:19:29.000
the ulama have said it is a sign

00:19:29.000 --> 00:19:32.480
that somewhere down the line they have consumed haram,

00:19:32.480 --> 00:19:34.920
either riba or either something

00:19:34.920 --> 00:19:36.600
that has earned the wrath of Allah

00:19:36.600 --> 00:19:38.360
that they have put into their mouth.

00:19:38.360 --> 00:19:40.320
Where did we get this from?

00:19:40.320 --> 00:19:46.440
فَأَكَلَى مِنْهَا فَبَدَتْ لَهُمَا سَوْأَتُهُمَا

00:19:46.440 --> 00:19:47.680
Allahu akbar.

00:19:47.680 --> 00:19:50.480
Adam and Hawwa, when they ate haram,

00:19:50.480 --> 00:19:51.960
their shame was exposed.

00:19:51.960 --> 00:19:53.240
You find they now,

00:19:53.240 --> 00:19:54.800
everything that was supposed to be covered

00:19:54.800 --> 00:19:56.240
began to become exposed.

00:19:56.240 --> 00:19:58.000
And the same happens to us now.

00:19:58.000 --> 00:20:00.920
Eat haram and you feel like uncovering your legs.

00:20:00.920 --> 00:20:02.200
What happens? You want to uncover.

00:20:02.200 --> 00:20:05.520
You don't get peace unless your hair is open.

00:20:05.520 --> 00:20:07.920
Something somewhere down the line is wrong.

00:20:07.960 --> 00:20:10.680
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us a turning point.

00:20:10.680 --> 00:20:12.880
I know what I have said is very heavy,

00:20:12.880 --> 00:20:15.120
but wallahi sometimes we need a push

00:20:15.120 --> 00:20:19.040
before we can actually obey the commands of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:20:19.040 --> 00:20:21.400
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala write this for us

00:20:21.400 --> 00:20:22.240
and not against us.

00:20:22.240 --> 00:20:24.760
May He make us from those whose hearts are softened

00:20:24.760 --> 00:20:26.200
when we hear something like this

00:20:26.200 --> 00:20:27.440
and not from amongst those

00:20:27.440 --> 00:20:30.800
whose hearts become even more hardened.

00:20:30.800 --> 00:20:33.320
So Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala has blessed us

00:20:33.320 --> 00:20:35.800
by revealing these as the first verses.

00:20:35.840 --> 00:20:39.520
And here there are some secrets of the creation of man,

00:20:39.520 --> 00:20:40.880
how man was created.

00:20:40.880 --> 00:20:42.120
These people of Quraish,

00:20:42.120 --> 00:20:45.000
they had no clue before how man was created.

00:20:45.000 --> 00:20:46.600
They did not know the beginning.

00:20:46.600 --> 00:20:48.200
They never believed in anything

00:20:48.200 --> 00:20:50.560
besides their idols and stones and so on.

00:20:50.560 --> 00:20:52.160
It was just the people of the book,

00:20:52.160 --> 00:20:54.520
the Jews and the Christians who were before,

00:20:54.520 --> 00:20:56.400
who had the correct knowledge

00:20:56.400 --> 00:20:59.080
of how man was created and so on.

00:20:59.080 --> 00:21:02.120
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless us all.

00:21:02.120 --> 00:21:04.400
So what happened to Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:21:04.400 --> 00:21:06.280
at that stage?

00:21:06.280 --> 00:21:08.920
Amazingly, he was now cold.

00:21:08.920 --> 00:21:12.560
He was worried in awe, we would say.

00:21:12.560 --> 00:21:14.640
He rushed down from the mount.

00:21:14.640 --> 00:21:16.960
Jibril alayhi salam had disappeared

00:21:16.960 --> 00:21:18.520
and this man rushes down.

00:21:18.520 --> 00:21:20.160
Where did he go?

00:21:20.160 --> 00:21:22.800
He went to the one whom he trusted the most

00:21:22.800 --> 00:21:24.720
at the time, his own beloved wife.

00:21:24.720 --> 00:21:27.360
How many of us, the most trustworthy to us

00:21:27.360 --> 00:21:30.250
are our wives?

00:21:30.250 --> 00:21:31.890
Don't worry, if your answer is no,

00:21:31.890 --> 00:21:34.770
we ask the wives, why is the answer no?

00:21:34.770 --> 00:21:36.170
Allahu akbar.

00:21:36.170 --> 00:21:37.370
So it's not only your fault.

00:21:37.370 --> 00:21:38.690
Sometimes it's even her fault

00:21:38.690 --> 00:21:41.610
because remember nowadays both of us

00:21:41.610 --> 00:21:43.090
need a lot of attention.

00:21:43.090 --> 00:21:45.290
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness.

00:21:45.290 --> 00:21:46.170
When I say attention,

00:21:46.170 --> 00:21:48.050
I'm talking of panel beating.

00:21:48.050 --> 00:21:50.050
I'm not talking of attention as in,

00:21:50.050 --> 00:21:52.850
you know, giving someone as much attention as possible.

00:21:52.850 --> 00:21:54.570
No, that is there.

00:21:54.570 --> 00:21:57.290
But we require correction, both of us.

00:21:57.290 --> 00:21:58.730
No one party can say,

00:21:58.730 --> 00:22:00.010
no, she's wrong, I'm right.

00:22:00.010 --> 00:22:01.010
He's wrong, I'm right.

00:22:01.010 --> 00:22:03.490
No, it takes two, subhanallah.

00:22:03.490 --> 00:22:05.250
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless us

00:22:05.250 --> 00:22:06.090
and open our doors.

00:22:06.090 --> 00:22:08.210
With Muhammad salallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:22:08.210 --> 00:22:10.330
he was such an upright man.

00:22:10.330 --> 00:22:11.450
When he ran down,

00:22:11.450 --> 00:22:13.370
he knew he could trust his wife.

00:22:13.370 --> 00:22:14.330
Today they say,

00:22:14.330 --> 00:22:16.530
you tell your wife something the whole dunya knows.

00:22:16.530 --> 00:22:18.290
I hope that's not the case with us.

00:22:18.290 --> 00:22:20.010
But they say, you want to spread news?

00:22:20.010 --> 00:22:21.010
It's email.

00:22:21.010 --> 00:22:22.730
Faster than email is female.

00:22:22.730 --> 00:22:25.210
Allahu akbar, Allah protect us.

00:22:25.210 --> 00:22:26.690
I hope that's not true.

00:22:26.690 --> 00:22:28.610
But sometimes this is what goes on.

00:22:28.610 --> 00:22:31.330
When someone has entrusted you with a secret,

00:22:31.330 --> 00:22:32.570
you take it to the grave.

00:22:32.570 --> 00:22:35.770
Believe me, you take it to the grave.

00:22:35.770 --> 00:22:36.650
Look at the quality.

00:22:36.650 --> 00:22:38.690
Muhammad salallahu alayhi wa sallam rushing down.

00:22:38.690 --> 00:22:39.810
What does he say?

00:22:39.810 --> 00:22:41.770
He comes down and he is sweating.

00:22:41.770 --> 00:22:43.450
And he is now feeling cold.

00:22:43.450 --> 00:22:44.850
And he is now in awe.

00:22:44.850 --> 00:22:45.970
And he is shivering.

00:22:45.970 --> 00:22:46.650
And he is saying,

00:22:46.650 --> 00:22:48.650
zammilooni, zammilooni,

00:22:48.650 --> 00:22:50.290
cover me, cover me.

00:22:50.290 --> 00:22:51.210
What has happened?

00:22:51.210 --> 00:22:52.690
His wife, beloved,

00:22:52.690 --> 00:22:55.250
Khadijah binti Khuwairid radiallahu anha

00:22:55.250 --> 00:22:57.050
immediately covers him.

00:22:57.050 --> 00:22:58.570
And she says, what is happening?

00:22:58.570 --> 00:22:59.410
What is wrong?

00:22:59.410 --> 00:23:01.450
And he narrates what had happened.

00:23:01.450 --> 00:23:02.210
And she says,

00:23:02.210 --> 00:23:06.290
kalla wallahi laa yukhzeekallahu abada

00:23:06.290 --> 00:23:07.770
Nay, never.

00:23:07.770 --> 00:23:10.050
Allah will never ever let you down.

00:23:10.050 --> 00:23:12.010
Nothing bad can happen to you.

00:23:12.010 --> 00:23:13.890
You are such an upright man.

00:23:13.890 --> 00:23:15.610
You assist those in need.

00:23:15.610 --> 00:23:17.530
You fulfill your family ties.

00:23:17.530 --> 00:23:19.410
You help the widows and the orphans.

00:23:19.410 --> 00:23:21.810
You always are out helping people.

00:23:21.810 --> 00:23:23.930
You have such great character and conduct.

00:23:23.930 --> 00:23:26.250
And she began singing praise.

00:23:26.250 --> 00:23:27.410
Why singing praise?

00:23:27.410 --> 00:23:29.890
Because this man was indeed the one

00:23:29.890 --> 00:23:33.250
who was really as she was mentioning.

00:23:33.250 --> 00:23:34.250
With us, your wife tells you,

00:23:34.250 --> 00:23:36.010
oh, you're such a wonderful man.

00:23:36.010 --> 00:23:36.850
But inside, she knows,

00:23:36.850 --> 00:23:39.210
I have to say this because I need something.

00:23:39.210 --> 00:23:40.770
It happens sometimes.

00:23:40.770 --> 00:23:42.330
If you ask her,

00:23:42.330 --> 00:23:43.170
you love me the most,

00:23:43.170 --> 00:23:44.930
she says, I love you the most.

00:23:44.930 --> 00:23:46.570
Insha'Allah, I hope it's the case.

00:23:46.570 --> 00:23:47.890
But sometimes she has to say it

00:23:47.890 --> 00:23:49.690
because what option does she have?

00:23:49.690 --> 00:23:51.050
Allahu akbar.

00:23:51.050 --> 00:23:53.010
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala save us.

00:23:53.010 --> 00:23:54.530
With her, she was honest.

00:23:54.530 --> 00:23:56.490
This was a time of need.

00:23:56.490 --> 00:23:58.170
And she knew the man is upright.

00:23:58.170 --> 00:23:59.250
What has he ever done?

00:23:59.250 --> 00:24:01.290
He's been a person who's concerned.

00:24:01.290 --> 00:24:02.930
He worships not the idols.

00:24:02.930 --> 00:24:04.610
Never has he worshiped an idol.

00:24:04.610 --> 00:24:05.490
He didn't drink.

00:24:05.490 --> 00:24:07.050
His tongue was so clean.

00:24:07.050 --> 00:24:07.930
He never swore.

00:24:07.930 --> 00:24:09.330
He never spoke slang.

00:24:09.330 --> 00:24:11.090
May Allah protect us from slang.

00:24:11.090 --> 00:24:13.970
It reduces the value and respect of an individual

00:24:13.970 --> 00:24:15.010
when he speaks slang,

00:24:15.010 --> 00:24:16.330
no matter who it is.

00:24:16.330 --> 00:24:17.930
And that is in the hadith of Rasulullah

00:24:17.930 --> 00:24:19.330
sallallahu alayhi wasallam.

00:24:19.330 --> 00:24:20.730
We, including myself,

00:24:20.730 --> 00:24:22.370
we are guilty sometimes of what?

00:24:22.370 --> 00:24:24.010
Uttering a word or two of slang,

00:24:24.010 --> 00:24:25.610
just to make it sound lighter

00:24:25.610 --> 00:24:27.170
and to bring it closer to the heart.

00:24:27.170 --> 00:24:28.410
We should try and avoid that.

00:24:28.410 --> 00:24:29.890
Speak clear language.

00:24:29.890 --> 00:24:32.090
And you don't need to speak so difficult language

00:24:32.090 --> 00:24:33.770
that people don't understand you.

00:24:33.770 --> 00:24:35.850
Speak in a way that everyone can comprehend

00:24:35.850 --> 00:24:36.690
and understand.

00:24:36.690 --> 00:24:38.210
Subhanallah.

00:24:38.210 --> 00:24:41.370
So she mentioned so many of his good qualities

00:24:41.370 --> 00:24:43.050
and she says, don't worry, don't worry.

00:24:43.050 --> 00:24:44.770
As she is covering him,

00:24:44.770 --> 00:24:46.010
she then decides,

00:24:46.010 --> 00:24:48.450
let me do this man a favor

00:24:48.450 --> 00:24:51.850
by taking him to my cousin Waraka ibn Nawfal.

00:24:51.850 --> 00:24:54.410
He was a man who read and wrote.

00:24:54.410 --> 00:24:57.250
He was very well-versed, highly educated.

00:24:57.250 --> 00:24:58.370
He was an alim,

00:24:58.370 --> 00:24:59.890
according to what we would say.

00:24:59.890 --> 00:25:01.930
Alim meaning he had knowledge of the deen

00:25:01.930 --> 00:25:03.090
and the religion.

00:25:03.090 --> 00:25:04.490
And he read the previous books

00:25:04.490 --> 00:25:05.330
and he had links

00:25:05.330 --> 00:25:07.250
with some of the people of the book.

00:25:07.250 --> 00:25:09.210
And so when Khadija binti Khuwailid

00:25:09.210 --> 00:25:11.090
radiallahu anha took this man,

00:25:11.090 --> 00:25:13.130
immediately, the husband, imagine,

00:25:13.130 --> 00:25:14.850
he was 40 years old.

00:25:14.850 --> 00:25:17.730
We said 21st of Ramadan.

00:25:17.730 --> 00:25:19.810
She was 55 years old,

00:25:19.810 --> 00:25:21.850
according to the bulk of the narrations.

00:25:21.850 --> 00:25:22.970
And what happened is,

00:25:22.970 --> 00:25:25.570
she's now taking her husband and going.

00:25:25.570 --> 00:25:28.010
They had had children, subhanallah.

00:25:28.010 --> 00:25:29.930
They had already had their children,

00:25:29.930 --> 00:25:30.890
subhanallah.

00:25:30.890 --> 00:25:33.290
And she is taking him

00:25:33.290 --> 00:25:35.570
and going to Waraka ibn Nawfal.

00:25:35.570 --> 00:25:36.810
And when they went, she says,

00:25:36.810 --> 00:25:39.930
oh, my cousin, listen to my husband.

00:25:39.930 --> 00:25:41.410
What has happened to him?

00:25:41.410 --> 00:25:43.330
So Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:25:43.330 --> 00:25:46.130
narrates the story to Waraka ibn Nawfal.

00:25:46.130 --> 00:25:49.370
Waraka was a man who was awaiting prophethood.

00:25:49.370 --> 00:25:51.570
He knew that the prophet is about to come

00:25:51.570 --> 00:25:53.850
any minute now in this region.

00:25:53.850 --> 00:25:55.730
He was also one of them who was waiting.

00:25:55.730 --> 00:25:58.010
So when he was told a man came to me,

00:25:58.010 --> 00:25:59.450
the angel came to me,

00:25:59.450 --> 00:26:00.330
and this is what happened.

00:26:00.330 --> 00:26:02.090
He revealed to me, iqra.

00:26:02.090 --> 00:26:03.770
Who was the first person

00:26:03.770 --> 00:26:06.250
who heard the words of revelation?

00:26:06.250 --> 00:26:08.330
Besides Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:26:08.330 --> 00:26:10.890
hearing it straight from Jibreel alayhi salam,

00:26:10.890 --> 00:26:12.530
it was Khadija.

00:26:12.530 --> 00:26:15.330
Khadija binti Khuwailid radiallahu anha.

00:26:15.330 --> 00:26:17.130
She heard these verses.

00:26:17.130 --> 00:26:19.210
So she was the first human being

00:26:19.210 --> 00:26:21.490
to listen to verses of the Quran

00:26:21.490 --> 00:26:24.330
after Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam.

00:26:24.330 --> 00:26:26.370
And she took this man to Waraka

00:26:26.370 --> 00:26:27.930
and Waraka heard the verses

00:26:27.930 --> 00:26:29.170
and he says, no,

00:26:29.170 --> 00:26:31.690
that is definitely the angel

00:26:31.690 --> 00:26:32.930
that came to Moses

00:26:32.930 --> 00:26:34.810
and the angel that came to Jesus.

00:26:34.810 --> 00:26:36.970
May peace be upon them all.

00:26:36.970 --> 00:26:38.170
Musa alayhi salam,

00:26:38.170 --> 00:26:39.930
Isa alayhi salatu was salam.

00:26:39.930 --> 00:26:41.730
That is the same angel,

00:26:41.730 --> 00:26:44.690
Jibreel alayhi salatu was salam.

00:26:44.690 --> 00:26:46.730
And if this man is saying the truth,

00:26:46.730 --> 00:26:49.450
then very soon he will be sent to his people.

00:26:49.450 --> 00:26:53.330
And I wish I had had youth in me

00:26:53.330 --> 00:26:55.050
to be there the day

00:26:55.050 --> 00:26:59.130
that he will be driven away from his own people.

00:26:59.130 --> 00:27:01.490
So Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam looks

00:27:01.490 --> 00:27:04.410
and he is now confused.

00:27:06.410 --> 00:27:09.970
Are they going to boot me out, my people?

00:27:09.970 --> 00:27:12.810
He says, I wish I will be there

00:27:12.810 --> 00:27:16.290
the day your people kick you out.

00:27:16.290 --> 00:27:18.490
Your own clan, tribesmen,

00:27:18.490 --> 00:27:20.690
I wish I will be there that day.

00:27:20.690 --> 00:27:22.730
Now remember, this was just revelation.

00:27:22.730 --> 00:27:24.210
This was prophethood.

00:27:24.210 --> 00:27:25.970
Allah did not instruct him yet

00:27:25.970 --> 00:27:27.250
to go out and preach.

00:27:27.250 --> 00:27:29.050
No, that hadn't yet come.

00:27:29.050 --> 00:27:30.410
This was only prophethood.

00:27:30.410 --> 00:27:31.650
It was the beginning.

00:27:31.650 --> 00:27:33.290
And Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:27:33.290 --> 00:27:35.770
was being calmed down by his wife.

00:27:35.770 --> 00:27:39.050
And Allah had placed her so strategically

00:27:39.050 --> 00:27:41.530
because she had had the qualities

00:27:41.530 --> 00:27:44.610
that were needed to really calm this man

00:27:44.610 --> 00:27:47.170
and to be a comfort and support for him

00:27:47.170 --> 00:27:48.730
at that particular time.

00:27:48.730 --> 00:27:51.010
No one but her would have done that.

00:27:51.010 --> 00:27:53.410
Look at how his business deals

00:27:53.410 --> 00:27:54.730
brought him to this woman

00:27:54.730 --> 00:27:56.570
and how this woman was also prepared

00:27:56.570 --> 00:27:58.210
by Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:27:58.210 --> 00:27:59.850
for this particular purpose.

00:28:00.810 --> 00:28:02.450
Radhiallahu anha.

00:28:02.450 --> 00:28:03.410
So what happened?

00:28:03.410 --> 00:28:05.330
He says, yes.

00:28:05.330 --> 00:28:08.210
Anyone who has come with anything

00:28:08.210 --> 00:28:10.290
similar to what you have come with

00:28:10.290 --> 00:28:12.650
has been fought and fought heavily.

00:28:14.010 --> 00:28:15.410
Allahu Akbar.

00:28:15.410 --> 00:28:17.370
Anyone who has brought prophethood

00:28:17.370 --> 00:28:18.610
and come to correct people

00:28:18.610 --> 00:28:20.730
has been fought up to today.

00:28:20.730 --> 00:28:25.010
Nearly every society and community on the globe.

00:28:25.010 --> 00:28:26.890
Whenever there is a man who gets up

00:28:26.890 --> 00:28:29.010
and tells them as is,

00:28:29.010 --> 00:28:30.850
there are a few people who fight that man.

00:28:30.850 --> 00:28:31.930
Always.

00:28:31.930 --> 00:28:33.250
Nearly every...

00:28:33.250 --> 00:28:34.130
I hope we're taking out

00:28:34.130 --> 00:28:35.650
a few good societies from there.

00:28:35.650 --> 00:28:37.930
Nearly every community.

00:28:37.930 --> 00:28:39.890
When a man comes and warns people

00:28:39.890 --> 00:28:41.210
and tells them and gives them

00:28:41.210 --> 00:28:43.410
a bit of what we would term today,

00:28:43.410 --> 00:28:44.930
you know, a true word,

00:28:44.930 --> 00:28:47.570
a word of advice, subhanallah.

00:28:47.570 --> 00:28:49.250
People don't like it sometimes.

00:28:49.250 --> 00:28:50.730
You know, you get the haughty

00:28:50.730 --> 00:28:52.650
who don't want to be told.

00:28:52.650 --> 00:28:53.970
Sometimes you have in a masjid,

00:28:53.970 --> 00:28:56.410
they tell you don't talk about interest here.

00:28:56.410 --> 00:28:58.330
Don't talk about music here.

00:28:58.330 --> 00:29:00.250
Don't talk about adultery here.

00:29:00.250 --> 00:29:03.850
Don't talk about illegitimate children here.

00:29:03.850 --> 00:29:04.930
What?

00:29:04.930 --> 00:29:06.530
I have come across this.

00:29:06.530 --> 00:29:07.730
I don't know if you have.

00:29:07.730 --> 00:29:08.850
Why would they do that?

00:29:08.850 --> 00:29:10.330
Because they have the clout

00:29:10.330 --> 00:29:11.370
and they're all involved

00:29:11.370 --> 00:29:13.010
in that type of misbehavior.

00:29:13.010 --> 00:29:13.970
They don't want to be told.

00:29:13.970 --> 00:29:15.170
When they come to the masjid,

00:29:15.170 --> 00:29:16.330
they want it to just be

00:29:16.330 --> 00:29:18.050
smoothing to the ears.

00:29:18.050 --> 00:29:19.050
Come and listen to,

00:29:19.050 --> 00:29:20.690
read Salah, give Zakah,

00:29:20.690 --> 00:29:21.810
go for Hajj,

00:29:21.810 --> 00:29:23.570
do this, do that, and that's it.

00:29:23.570 --> 00:29:25.410
Don't even say be truthful.

00:29:25.410 --> 00:29:27.210
Stop lying, stop eating interest.

00:29:27.210 --> 00:29:28.250
Don't even say that

00:29:28.250 --> 00:29:29.290
because you're going to trample

00:29:29.290 --> 00:29:30.930
the feet of those who are haughty.

00:29:30.930 --> 00:29:32.650
Allah protect us.

00:29:32.650 --> 00:29:35.090
This is the downfall of society.

00:29:35.090 --> 00:29:36.530
This is what happened.

00:29:36.530 --> 00:29:37.850
Waraka bin Nawfal says

00:29:37.850 --> 00:29:40.850
anyone who came with this message

00:29:40.850 --> 00:29:43.930
was fought by their own people, subhanallah.

00:29:43.930 --> 00:29:45.170
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:29:45.170 --> 00:29:46.290
not make us those

00:29:46.290 --> 00:29:47.290
who fight the messengers

00:29:47.290 --> 00:29:49.370
who come to us.

00:29:49.370 --> 00:29:50.090
Allahu Akbar.

00:29:50.090 --> 00:29:52.210
So here Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:29:52.210 --> 00:29:54.930
is told that you know what?

00:29:54.930 --> 00:29:56.610
A time will come

00:29:56.610 --> 00:29:58.050
when Jibreel will come again

00:29:58.050 --> 00:29:59.850
and he will give you revelation

00:29:59.850 --> 00:30:01.250
and I wish I'm there.

00:30:01.250 --> 00:30:03.050
If I am alive, Waraka says,

00:30:03.050 --> 00:30:05.450
I will support you with full support,

00:30:05.450 --> 00:30:07.290
full backing of mine you will have.

00:30:07.290 --> 00:30:09.850
Sadly, few days later he passed away.

00:30:09.850 --> 00:30:11.170
Waraka bin Nawfal.

00:30:11.170 --> 00:30:13.450
Only Allah knows his position.

00:30:13.450 --> 00:30:15.050
Only Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:30:15.050 --> 00:30:16.610
knows exactly where he is.

00:30:16.610 --> 00:30:18.050
There are some narrations

00:30:18.050 --> 00:30:19.930
which make mention of his forgiveness

00:30:19.930 --> 00:30:20.770
and so on.

00:30:20.770 --> 00:30:22.330
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:30:22.330 --> 00:30:23.690
treat him with his mercy

00:30:23.690 --> 00:30:25.130
and may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:30:25.130 --> 00:30:26.650
treat us all with his mercy.

00:30:26.650 --> 00:30:28.930
So this was Waraka bin Nawfal.

00:30:28.930 --> 00:30:30.930
So now Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam,

00:30:30.930 --> 00:30:32.850
him and his wife, subhanallah,

00:30:32.850 --> 00:30:35.130
Khadija binti Khuwailid radiallahu anha,

00:30:35.130 --> 00:30:36.650
she believed completely

00:30:36.650 --> 00:30:39.090
there was no question of a question.

00:30:39.090 --> 00:30:41.050
No need to ask

00:30:41.050 --> 00:30:43.850
because she knew what had gone on.

00:30:43.850 --> 00:30:47.650
So she was the first who actually believed.

00:30:47.650 --> 00:30:48.570
Now what had happened?

00:30:48.570 --> 00:30:50.250
There was a period of time,

00:30:50.250 --> 00:30:53.450
a few days wherein revelation stopped.

00:30:53.450 --> 00:30:54.850
Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:30:54.850 --> 00:30:55.970
would go back

00:30:55.970 --> 00:30:58.450
and he would meditate once again.

00:30:58.450 --> 00:30:59.450
Some narrations say

00:30:59.450 --> 00:31:00.850
it was a very long period of time.

00:31:00.850 --> 00:31:03.450
No, the most correct narrations

00:31:03.450 --> 00:31:06.650
make mention of a 10-day gap.

00:31:06.650 --> 00:31:07.890
10-day gap meaning

00:31:07.890 --> 00:31:10.250
21st of Ramadan

00:31:10.250 --> 00:31:12.050
up to the first of Shawwal.

00:31:12.050 --> 00:31:13.250
Now if you take a careful look,

00:31:13.250 --> 00:31:14.650
he used to go every day

00:31:14.650 --> 00:31:16.650
and meditate in seclusion.

00:31:16.650 --> 00:31:20.850
We are all encouraged

00:31:20.850 --> 00:31:22.450
to engage in Ibadah

00:31:22.450 --> 00:31:25.450
and worship Allah in seclusion as well.

00:31:25.450 --> 00:31:26.450
And do you know what?

00:31:26.450 --> 00:31:28.650
Those particular 10 days

00:31:28.650 --> 00:31:30.050
are actually a Sunnah

00:31:30.050 --> 00:31:31.650
to engage in I'tikaaf.

00:31:31.650 --> 00:31:32.650
I'tikaaf meaning

00:31:32.650 --> 00:31:33.650
you sit in seclusion

00:31:33.650 --> 00:31:35.650
in the house of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:31:35.650 --> 00:31:37.250
pondering over your weakness,

00:31:37.250 --> 00:31:38.650
how you can correct yourself,

00:31:38.650 --> 00:31:40.250
how you can be improved

00:31:40.250 --> 00:31:42.050
and you worship Allah alone

00:31:42.050 --> 00:31:43.650
and you increase your tilawa,

00:31:43.650 --> 00:31:44.650
recitation of the Quran,

00:31:44.650 --> 00:31:45.650
understanding of it,

00:31:45.650 --> 00:31:47.050
your Salah and so on.

00:31:47.050 --> 00:31:48.250
May Allah make us from those

00:31:48.250 --> 00:31:51.050
who can engage in this I'tikaaf.

00:31:51.050 --> 00:31:52.850
So the Prophet sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:31:52.850 --> 00:31:54.050
from the 21st,

00:31:54.050 --> 00:31:55.850
the 22nd, the 23rd,

00:31:55.850 --> 00:31:58.450
he was waiting for revelation to come again

00:31:58.450 --> 00:32:02.250
as per what Waraqa ibn Nawfal told him.

00:32:02.250 --> 00:32:04.850
And what happened?

00:32:04.850 --> 00:32:06.050
The revelation did not come.

00:32:06.050 --> 00:32:07.450
So Nabi sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:32:07.450 --> 00:32:09.450
was getting a bit worried.

00:32:09.450 --> 00:32:12.050
And then on the 1st of Shawwal

00:32:12.050 --> 00:32:13.050
it is reported that

00:32:13.050 --> 00:32:15.850
that is when he was walking this hadith,

00:32:15.850 --> 00:32:18.050
this hadith of Jabir radiallahu anhu

00:32:18.050 --> 00:32:20.050
which is mentioned in Sahih al-Bukhari

00:32:20.050 --> 00:32:22.250
where Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:32:22.250 --> 00:32:23.850
says whilst I was walking

00:32:23.850 --> 00:32:24.650
I looked up

00:32:24.650 --> 00:32:27.250
and I saw the angel Jibril

00:32:27.250 --> 00:32:29.050
in his original form.

00:32:29.050 --> 00:32:30.850
You know what the original form is?

00:32:30.850 --> 00:32:32.050
Nabi sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:32:32.050 --> 00:32:33.650
saw Jibril many times

00:32:33.650 --> 00:32:35.650
but most of the times

00:32:35.850 --> 00:32:37.650
he was in the form of a man,

00:32:37.650 --> 00:32:38.950
a very handsome man.

00:32:38.950 --> 00:32:40.950
And when he came in the form of a man

00:32:40.950 --> 00:32:43.050
there were times when his companions

00:32:43.050 --> 00:32:45.150
have also seen him.

00:32:45.150 --> 00:32:46.250
Like the ones he came

00:32:46.250 --> 00:32:48.450
and he sat with Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:32:48.450 --> 00:32:50.250
and he was asking him some questions.

00:32:50.250 --> 00:32:51.850
And then when he went away

00:32:51.850 --> 00:32:53.250
the sahabah radiallahu anhu

00:32:53.250 --> 00:32:55.250
say that we saw this man coming

00:32:55.250 --> 00:32:56.450
he had white clothes,

00:32:56.450 --> 00:32:57.650
he had black hair

00:32:57.650 --> 00:32:58.850
with nobody knew him

00:32:58.850 --> 00:33:01.050
which means he was not from anywhere near

00:33:01.050 --> 00:33:03.050
but he looked like he had not

00:33:03.050 --> 00:33:05.450
undertaken any journey whatsoever

00:33:05.450 --> 00:33:07.850
and he came in and he sat with his knees

00:33:07.850 --> 00:33:09.050
right in front of

00:33:09.050 --> 00:33:11.250
with the knees of Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:33:11.250 --> 00:33:12.250
utmost respect

00:33:12.250 --> 00:33:13.550
he is asking questions

00:33:13.550 --> 00:33:14.650
when the answer comes

00:33:14.650 --> 00:33:16.150
he says yes you are right.

00:33:16.150 --> 00:33:17.550
And they say we were surprised

00:33:17.550 --> 00:33:19.150
how come this man is asking

00:33:19.150 --> 00:33:20.950
and he is also saying you are right.

00:33:20.950 --> 00:33:22.250
Imagine someone asks you

00:33:22.250 --> 00:33:23.050
how old are you

00:33:23.050 --> 00:33:24.050
and you say fifty

00:33:24.050 --> 00:33:25.050
and he says you are right

00:33:25.050 --> 00:33:25.750
Allahu akbar

00:33:25.750 --> 00:33:27.250
he says well why did you ask me?

00:33:27.250 --> 00:33:28.750
Allahu akbar

00:33:28.750 --> 00:33:31.150
So when he went away

00:33:31.150 --> 00:33:32.450
Nabi sallallahu alaihi wasallam says

00:33:32.450 --> 00:33:33.950
do you know who that was?

00:33:33.950 --> 00:33:35.350
They said Allah and His messenger

00:33:35.350 --> 00:33:36.250
said no best

00:33:36.250 --> 00:33:37.250
that was Jibreel

00:33:37.250 --> 00:33:40.050
he came to you to teach you your religion

00:33:40.050 --> 00:33:41.650
in the form of a Q&A

00:33:41.650 --> 00:33:42.650
Allahu akbar

00:33:42.650 --> 00:33:44.750
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala benefit us

00:33:44.750 --> 00:33:45.950
and may He grant us goodness.

00:33:45.950 --> 00:33:47.750
So when Nabi sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:33:47.750 --> 00:33:51.150
saw Jibreel alaihi wasallam

00:33:51.150 --> 00:33:52.350
he says I looked up

00:33:52.350 --> 00:33:54.150
and I saw

00:33:54.150 --> 00:33:55.950
Jibreel alaihi wasallam

00:33:55.950 --> 00:33:57.250
he covered the sky

00:33:57.250 --> 00:33:58.250
the whole sky

00:33:58.250 --> 00:33:59.550
in his original form

00:33:59.550 --> 00:34:00.650
he was seen twice

00:34:00.650 --> 00:34:01.950
by Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:34:01.950 --> 00:34:03.350
once

00:34:03.350 --> 00:34:04.650
was on this occasion

00:34:04.650 --> 00:34:05.750
that we are talking about

00:34:05.750 --> 00:34:08.850
when the second set of verses were revealed

00:34:08.850 --> 00:34:11.450
he had 600 wings

00:34:11.450 --> 00:34:14.350
each wing from the east to the west

00:34:14.350 --> 00:34:15.950
you cannot see where it starts

00:34:15.950 --> 00:34:17.650
and you cannot see where it ends

00:34:17.650 --> 00:34:18.550
subhanallah

00:34:18.550 --> 00:34:20.550
laahu 600 janah

00:34:20.550 --> 00:34:21.550
600 wings

00:34:21.550 --> 00:34:24.150
this angel Jibreel alaihi wasallam

00:34:24.150 --> 00:34:25.350
in his original form

00:34:25.350 --> 00:34:27.050
the second time Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:34:27.050 --> 00:34:29.150
saw him was Mi'raj

00:34:29.150 --> 00:34:30.550
I'm sure we all are aware

00:34:30.550 --> 00:34:32.250
of the incident of the ascension

00:34:32.250 --> 00:34:34.850
into the heavens of Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:34:34.850 --> 00:34:35.450
yes

00:34:35.450 --> 00:34:37.550
on that occasion also he saw

00:34:37.550 --> 00:34:39.350
Jibreel alaihi wasallam

00:34:39.350 --> 00:34:41.150
in his original form

00:34:41.150 --> 00:34:43.050
so when he saw this angel

00:34:43.050 --> 00:34:45.850
he immediately was in awe once again

00:34:45.850 --> 00:34:48.250
and he was concerned again

00:34:48.250 --> 00:34:50.650
he ran back to his home

00:34:50.650 --> 00:34:52.050
and as he is running

00:34:52.050 --> 00:34:53.750
